                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2002-10-13</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>The least the publisher could do was put a subtitle on the cover that says that this is a poorly structured book of strung together game reports one could find in the archive of the Boston Globe.<P>Sheesh. If a fifth grader handed this manuscript in, he would get a D. One sentence paragraphs, factual errors repeated throughout the book (i.e. Pats were in Superbowl XXXI, not XXX; Jets beat the Raiders to get the Pats first round bye - not Bills beat Jets, etc.), disconcerting game reviews where the second half is reviewed before the first half, cliches, etc.<P>The Pats' championship season deserved a lot better than this.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">The Pats!!</div>
                    <div>
